<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="56" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1572,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1572,1597]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Outline of the dorsal scutum beta-shaped in males and almost alpha-shaped in females (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1390,1572,1597]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[162,1422,761,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1422,761,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Platymessa h-inscriptum Mello-Leitão, 1941: 1. Male holotype (MNRJ 282), habitus, dorsal view. 2. Same, lateral view. 3. Male (ICN-AO 1186) habitus, frontal view. 4. Same, posterior view. 5. Male (MNRJ 58) proximal part of coxa IV showing groin warts, dorsal view. 6. Female (MNRJ 463) proximal part of coxa IV showing groin warts (or clavus inguinis = ci), dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052449/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1405,1421,1573,1597]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1847,1870]" captionTargetBox="[253,1319,193,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[253,1319,193,1793]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 18. Platymessa h-inscriptum Mello-Leitão, 1941: 7. Male holotype (MNRJ 282) habitus, dorsal view 8. Schematic outline of dorsal scutum of male. 9. Schematic outline of dorsal scutum of female. 10 – 18. Variation of the pattern of spots in dorsal scutum: (10,11,12,15,16) ♀♀ ICN-AO 1186, (13) ♂ ICN-AO 1186, (14,17) ♀♀ ICN-AO 1384, (18) ♂ ICN-AO 1384. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052451/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">7</figureCitation>
); coda longer in females (
<figureCitation box="[420,488,1608,1633]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1847,1870]" captionTargetBox="[253,1319,193,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[253,1319,193,1793]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 18. Platymessa h-inscriptum Mello-Leitão, 1941: 7. Male holotype (MNRJ 282) habitus, dorsal view 8. Schematic outline of dorsal scutum of male. 9. Schematic outline of dorsal scutum of female. 10 – 18. Variation of the pattern of spots in dorsal scutum: (10,11,12,15,16) ♀♀ ICN-AO 1186, (13) ♂ ICN-AO 1186, (14,17) ♀♀ ICN-AO 1384, (18) ♂ ICN-AO 1384. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052451/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); scutal area V with two small paramedian granules; yellowish white color markings of scutum as a ladder mask (a pair of divergent bars connected by parallel thinner blots over scutal grooves) over dark brown background, thinner blots sometimes dissociated. Dorso-apical apophysis of coxa IV as a blunt spine (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,1717,1742]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[162,1422,761,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1422,761,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Platymessa h-inscriptum Mello-Leitão, 1941: 1. Male holotype (MNRJ 282), habitus, dorsal view. 2. Same, lateral view. 3. Male (ICN-AO 1186) habitus, frontal view. 4. Same, posterior view. 5. Male (MNRJ 58) proximal part of coxa IV showing groin warts, dorsal view. 6. Female (MNRJ 463) proximal part of coxa IV showing groin warts (or clavus inguinis = ci), dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052449/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[244,260,1717,1741]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1847,1870]" captionTargetBox="[253,1319,193,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[253,1319,193,1793]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 18. Platymessa h-inscriptum Mello-Leitão, 1941: 7. Male holotype (MNRJ 282) habitus, dorsal view 8. Schematic outline of dorsal scutum of male. 9. Schematic outline of dorsal scutum of female. 10 – 18. Variation of the pattern of spots in dorsal scutum: (10,11,12,15,16) ♀♀ ICN-AO 1186, (13) ♂ ICN-AO 1186, (14,17) ♀♀ ICN-AO 1384, (18) ♂ ICN-AO 1384. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052451/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">7</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae monomorphic, weak, with marginal rows of acuminate tubercles of varied size on posterior border. Groin warts present, larger in female. Legs short and strong, femur III and IV slightly arched and with five longitudinal rows of small tubercles; basitarsomeres of leg I of male thicker than distitarsomeres but not swollen; cheliceral sockets shallow with well-marked lateral triangular projections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1572,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,914,1860,1886]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
Taxonomic background of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1941" box="[548,699,1860,1885]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Brachylibitia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[548,699,1860,1885]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Brachylibitia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1941" box="[777,906,1860,1885]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Platymessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
